Analysis of the Main Target Image  
• Block Count & Layers:  
  – There are three total blocks.  
  – They form two layers: the bottom layer is a single red arch block, and the top layer consists of two cubes (blue on the left, yellow on the right).  
• Spatial Arrangement:  
  – The red arch block sits on the ground with its curved opening running front‐to‐back.  
  – Directly on top of it, side by side, are the blue and yellow cubes. The blue cube is on the left (when viewed from the front), and the yellow cube on the right.  

Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary  
• Bottom Block: Red arch block from index 1 (matches the “front‐to‐back” arch orientation).  
• Top Blocks:  
  – Blue cube at index 9  
  – Yellow cube at index 13  

Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 1  
  Step2: Move block with index 9  
  Step3: Move block with index 13  
}
